column1: Baby Barnaby's////Came here for brunch on Sunday
column2: had to sign in on a clipboard and wait for a table to clear up but boy oh boy
column3: that wait was so worth it! Those green eggs(scrambled eggs with spinach
column5: jack cheese) served with yummy chicken apple sausage
column6: potatoes and wheat toast were the bomb!! This place is my new favorite brunch spot! The servers are super friendly! They have fresh squeezed orange juice-so refreshing! The place is tiny and parking was a little bit hard on the street but like I said
